1.5 Expected Impact

By unifying electrochemical feature engineering, advanced temporal modeling, physical constraints, uncertainty quantification, multi‑task learning, and domain adaptation, this thesis aims to set a new benchmark for battery health prognostics. The resulting framework will not only achieve superior accuracy and robustness but also provide the interpretability and reliability required for real‑world EV deployment. The cross‑chemistry domain adaptation capability, in particular, promises a universal battery health model that can be rapidly deployed across diverse fleets, accelerating the transition to electric mobility and enabling second‑life applications with confidence.

